<sect2 id="rndesktop">

  <title>Desktop</title>


  <sect3 id="rnlogin"><title>Login</title>
    <para>
     When you start your computer you will see the GNOME login screen, where you should enter your user name and password. This keeps your information safe and remembers your personal settings.
    </para>

  <figure id="rnscreenshot-login">
    <title>The GNOME Login screen</title>
      <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject><imagedata fileref="&urlfiguresbase;figure-login.png" format="PNG"/>
          </imageobject>
        <textobject><phrase>The GNOME Login screen</phrase></textobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
  </figure>
  
  </sect3>

  <sect3 id="rndesktop_start"><title>Desktop</title>
    <para>
     After you login, you will see the GNOME Desktop. Notice, in particular:
    
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>The panels at the top and bottom.</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>The Home icon at the top-left, and the trash can.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   </para>

  <figure id="rnscreenshot-desktop">
    <title>The GNOME Desktop</title>
      <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject><imagedata fileref="&urlfiguresbase;figure-desktop.png" format="PNG"/>
          </imageobject>
        <textobject><phrase>The GNOME Desktop</phrase></textobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
  </figure>

  <para>The Applications menu at the top left has a list of software, such as the web browser and the email reader.</para>
  
  </sect3>

</sect2>
